  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Educating 100,000 out of school kids via radio&amp;SMS</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">We enable rural Ugandan students of all ages to learn math and science remotely using widely accessible technologies: radios and keypad phones. We use a &quot;flipped classroom&quot; model where learners interact with content individually and then engage in a broadcast lesson with a teacher. We send content to users via robocalls and SMS. The learners answer questions, complete homework, and take quizzes via Unstructured Supplementary Service Data (USSD), a real-time SMS system that is free for the user.</narrative>
  </description>
